            <div type="translation">
                <p>No translation is offered for either inscription</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Macalister expanded the two Ogham characters he read to interpret the inscription as VASSO(G?) with uncertain grounds. Neither the Ogham nor the Roman-letter inscriptions were given further interpretation or translation. The Welsh Corpus is unconvinced of the presence of inscription, describing evidence for their presence today as<q>unconvincing</q> while also stating that <q>the assumption must be that the stone is prehistoric: certainly the kinds of legend frequently associated with such stones seems to have accumulated around it. One claims that whenever a cock crows, the stone moves off to drink in the river Nedd; in another the stone visits the river Mellte on Midsummer morning</q> (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 547; Grinsell 1976, 59).
                </p>
            </div>
